---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout>
    <section style="padding-top: 60px; border-bottom: none;">
        <div class="container reading" style="max-width: var(--container);">
            <span class="tag sanskrit">॥ ज्ञानम् संरचना ॥</span>
            <span class="tag">Knowledge</span>
            <h1>Knowledge <span class="highlight">Systems</span></h1>
            <p class="lead" style="max-width: 650px;">
                Build a structured knowledge environment that helps important information remain accessible, understandable, and useful over time.
            </p>
            <div style="display: flex; gap: 1rem; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
                <span style="font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace; font-size: 1.2rem; color: var(--accent);">Starting at ₹35,000</span>
                <span style="font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace; font-size: 1.2rem; color: var(--text-muted);">|</span>
                <span style="font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace; font-size: 1.2rem; color: var(--text-muted);">Timeline: 2–4 Weeks</span>
            </div>
            <p style="font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--text-muted); border-left: 2px solid var(--accent-dim); padding-left: 1rem;">
                Systems Audit Included — Every Knowledge Systems engagement begins with a Systems Audit and Discovery Process to ensure implementation decisions are based on evidence rather than assumptions.
            </p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section style="padding-top: 40px; border-bottom: none;">
        <div class="container reading" style="max-width: var(--container);">
            <h2>A Knowledge System Is More Than Documentation</h2>
            <p>Most organizations possess more information than they can effectively use. Documentation becomes fragmented. Research becomes difficult to find. Resources become disconnected. Important knowledge remains trapped inside individuals.</p>
            <p>Over time, information accumulates while understanding declines. A Knowledge System is designed to solve that problem.</p>
            <p>Instead of treating documentation, research, resources, and operational knowledge as separate challenges, we create a structured system that helps information remain accessible, maintainable, and useful over time.</p>

            <h2 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Common Problems</h2>
            <ul class="structural">
                <li>Documentation is incomplete</li>
                <li>Information is scattered across multiple tools</li>
                <li>Team members struggle to find resources</li>
                <li>Research becomes difficult to retrieve</li>
                <li>Knowledge depends on specific individuals</li>
                <li>Resources lack structure</li>
                <li>New team members take too long to learn</li>
                <li>Information grows faster than organization</li>
            </ul>
            <p>If several of these problems sound familiar, the issue is often structural rather than informational.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section style="padding-top: 40px; border-bottom: none;">
        <div class="container reading" style="max-width: var(--container);">
            <h2>Who This Is For</h2>
            <p>This engagement is designed for:</p>
            <ul class="structural">
                <li>Educators</li>
                <li>Researchers</li>
                <li>Consultants</li>
                <li>Knowledge Businesses</li>
                <li>Founder-Led Organizations</li>
                <li>Teams Managing Large Amounts Of Information</li>
                <li>Organizations With Documentation Challenges</li>
            </ul>
            <p>If important information exists but is difficult to find, maintain, transfer, or use, this engagement may be a good fit.</p>

            <h2 style="margin-top: 2rem;">What This Is Not</h2>
            <ul class="structural">
                <li>A collection of disconnected documents</li>
                <li>A folder cleanup exercise</li>
                <li>A one-time documentation project</li>
                <li>A knowledge base built without structure</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Knowledge Systems focus on organization, accessibility, maintainability, and long-term usefulness.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section style="padding-top: 40px; border-bottom: none;">
        <div class="container reading" style="max-width: var(--container);">
            <h2>What You'll Receive</h2>
            <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 1.5rem; margin-top: 1rem;">
                <div style="background: var(--surface); padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 12px; border: 1px solid var(--border);">
                    <h3 style="font-size: 1.1rem;">The Blueprint Layer</h3>
                    <ul style="list-style: none; color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 0.9rem;">
                        <li>• Knowledge Audit</li>
                        <li>• Knowledge Architecture</li>
                        <li>• Documentation Framework</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div style="background: var(--surface); padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 12px; border: 1px solid var(--border);">
                    <h3 style="font-size: 1.1rem;">The Operational Layer</h3>
                    <ul style="list-style: none; color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 0.9rem;">
                        <li>• Resource Organization System</li>
                        <li>• Maintenance Framework</li>
                        <li>• Knowledge Playbook</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <h2 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Example Knowledge Systems</h2>
            <ul class="structural">
                <li>Internal Knowledge Bases</li>
                <li>Research Libraries</li>
                <li>Documentation Systems</li>
                <li>SOP Repositories</li>
                <li>Learning Systems</li>
                <li>Resource Libraries</li>
                <li>Organizational Wikis</li>
                <li>Educational Archives</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section style="padding-top: 40px; border-bottom: none;">
        <div class="container reading" style="max-width: var(--container);">
            <h2>How The Process Works</h2>
            <ol style="color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 2;">
                <li><strong style="color: var(--text);">Step 1 — Systems Audit:</strong> Every project begins with a Systems Audit and Discovery Process.</li>
                <li><strong style="color: var(--text);">Step 2 — Discovery & Planning:</strong> Goals, priorities, information sources, and constraints are clarified.</li>
                <li><strong style="color: var(--text);">Step 3 — Knowledge Architecture Design:</strong> Information structures, documentation systems, and organizational frameworks are developed.</li>
                <li><strong style="color: var(--text);">Step 4 — Implementation:</strong> Approved recommendations are implemented according to project scope.</li>
                <li><strong style="color: var(--text);">Step 5 — Documentation & Handover:</strong> Documentation, guidance, and implementation notes are delivered.</li>
            </ol>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section style="padding-top: 40px; border-bottom: none;">
        <div class="container reading" style="max-width: var(--container);">
            <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
            <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.5rem;">
                <div>
                    <h3 style="font-size: 1.1rem;">Is this only for businesses?</h3>
                    <p style="font-size: 0.95rem;">No. Knowledge Systems can support educators, researchers, consultants, and organizations of various sizes.</p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h3 style="font-size: 1.1rem;">Do I need existing documentation?</h3>
                    <p style="font-size: 0.95rem;">No. Systems can be built from existing information or created from the ground up.</p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h3 style="font-size: 1.1rem;">Can this work with Notion?</h3>
                    <p style="font-size: 0.95rem;">Yes. Notion and other knowledge management platforms may be used when appropriate.</p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h3 style="font-size: 1.1rem;">What if our information exists across multiple tools?</h3>
                    <p style="font-size: 0.95rem;">That is common and often part of the problem being addressed. The core objective is creating a clear, unified structure across all existing information sources.</p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h3 style="font-size: 1.1rem;">Is every project accepted?</h3>
                    <p style="font-size: 0.95rem;">No. Projects are evaluated before engagement to ensure the goals, scope, and expected outcomes are an appropriate fit.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div style="margin-top: 2rem; background: var(--surface); padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 12px; border: 1px solid var(--border);">
                <h2 style="font-size: 1.5rem;">Build On A Strong Foundation</h2>
                <p>Information grows. Teams change. Context is lost. A well-designed Knowledge System helps important information remain accessible, understandable, and useful over time.</p>
                <p style="font-style: italic; color: var(--accent);">For qualifying projects, the audit investment is credited toward the project scope.</p>
                <a href="/work-with-aman/systems-audit" class="btn" style="margin-top: 1rem;">Request a Systems Audit</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</Layout>